Session 1: OWASP Top 10 (2021), Injection, XSS, Stored Procedure Injection
üîπ BASIC MCQs (10)
1. Which organization publishes the OWASP Top 10 list?
A. ISO
B. NIST
C. CERT-In
D. OWASP

2. Which OWASP Top 10 (2021) category includes SQL Injection?
A. Broken Authentication
B. Injection
C. Security Misconfiguration
D. Sensitive Data Exposure

3. SQL Injection mainly targets which component of a web application?
A. Web Server
B. Database
C. Client Browser
D. Firewall

4. Which character is MOST commonly used to comment out SQL queries?
A. #
B. --
C. /* */
D. All of the above

5. Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) occurs due to:
A. Improper input validation
B. Weak encryption
C. Open ports
D. Network sniffing

6. Which type of XSS is stored permanently on the server?
A. Reflected XSS
B. DOM-based XSS
C. Stored XSS
D. Blind XSS

7. Inclusion vulnerabilities allow attackers to:
A. Modify cookies
B. Execute remote files
C. Capture packets
D. Encrypt traffic

8. Which vulnerability allows execution of JavaScript in a victim‚Äôs browser?
A. SQL Injection
B. Command Injection
C. Cross-Site Scripting
D. CSRF

9. Stored Procedure Injection is dangerous because it:
A. Bypasses firewall
B. Executes precompiled SQL logic
C. Uses JavaScript
D. Affects DNS

10. Which is a primary goal of OWASP Top 10?
A. Malware detection
B. Awareness of web risks
C. Network monitoring
D. System hardening

üî∏ INTERMEDIATE MCQs (10)
11. Which payload can bypass a basic login form?
A. admin/admin
B. admin' OR '1'='1
C. admin && password
D. admin AND false

12. Which OWASP 2021 category includes Injection flaws?
A. A01
B. A02
C. A03
D. A05

13. Reflected XSS mainly occurs through:
A. Database storage
B. URL parameters
C. Cookies
D. Server logs

14. Which function helps prevent XSS in PHP?
A. md5()
B. htmlspecialchars()
C. base64_encode()
D. strlen()

15. SQL Injection is possible when user input is:
A. Hashed
B. Sanitized
C. Directly concatenated into queries
D. Encrypted

16. Which inclusion attack allows loading files from remote servers?
A. LFI
B. RFI
C. XSS
D. CSRF

17. Stored procedure injection is MOST likely when procedures use:
A. Static SQL
B. Dynamic SQL
C. Parameterized queries
D. ORM frameworks

18. Which HTTP method is commonly abused for XSS?
A. GET
B. POST
C. PUT
D. DELETE

19. Which OWASP control BEST mitigates Injection attacks?
A. CAPTCHA
B. Input validation
C. Logging
D. Encryption

20. Blind XSS is difficult to detect because:
A. No immediate response is seen
B. It uses SSL
C. It is client-side only
D. It affects cookies only

üî∫ ADVANCED MCQs (10) ‚Äì CCEE TRICKY ZONE
