B. SQL login bypass queries
C. Session fixation
D. Port scanning

29. Inclusion vulnerabilities mainly arise due to:
A. Improper file handling
B. Weak encryption
C. Open ports
D. DNS misconfiguration

30. Which OWASP principle is violated when user input executes as code?
A. Least privilege
B. Trust boundary violation
C. Defense in depth
D. Availability

